## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points
1. **Blending difficulty** - Users struggle achieving smooth gradient transitions; colors look patchy or have harsh lines instead of seamless fade
2. **Technique confusion** - Overwhelming options (airbrush, sponge, eyeshadow, blooming gel, pigment powder) leave users unsure which method works best for beginners
3. **Color selection anxiety** - Uncertainty about which color combinations create romantic Valentine vibe vs clashing or looking muddy when blended
4. **Mess and overflow** - Gel polish getting on skin/cuticles during sponge application; difficulty keeping work area clean
5. **Opacity inconsistency** - Center too faint or edges too harsh; difficulty controlling pigment concentration for proper aura effect

### User Sentiment
Excited but intimidated—users love the dreamy aesthetic but fear technique complexity. Craving validation that DIY results can match salon quality.

